exports[`Component: Review should render the correct layout 1`] = `
<Fragment>
  <FrequentlyAskedQuestionsstyles__HelpAnswer>
    <div>
      <p>
        At this stage DEPS understands the extracted data for enrichment and apply algorithms and
  auto-correction to improve the quality.
      </p>
      <p>
        After extraction stage data needs to be cleaned up, reviewed, and meet business requirements.
  To improve accuracy, we apply validation and consolidation steps.
      </p>
      <p>
        After data extraction the user can manually review the document.
  During the validation process, errors are corrected, warnings are viewed, and additional data can be extracted.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>
          Manual review
        </b>
      </p>
      <p>
        Review is a manual process, at this stage user compares parsed data with original document and corrects mistakes.
  DEPS provide UI for data review and correction; highlight data with low confidence of extraction; display validation results.
      </p>
      <p>
        After data extraction the user can manually review the document. During the validation process,
  errors are corrected, warnings are viewed, and additional data can be extracted.
      </p>
    </div>
    <Reviewstyles__StyledReviewProcessImage />
  </FrequentlyAskedQuestionsstyles__HelpAnswer>
  <div>
    <p>
      If the user corrects the data himself in manual mode, the system marks these fields as 'Modified by the user'.
  After checking and correcting the data, the user clicks the 'Complete Review' button.
    </p>
    <p>
      Review is complete, data is ready for export.
    </p>
    <p>
      Low confidence data highlighted with 'CL' icon. Confidence Level is displayed in the range from 0 to 1,
  for example, a value of 0.49 means 49%. If the level is low, then the user needs to double-check the field data.
    </p>
  </div>
  <Reviewstyles__StyledModifiedByImage />
  <Reviewstyles__StyledConfidenceLevelImage />
  <FrequentlyAskedQuestionsstyles__HelpAnswer>
    <div>
      <p>
        <b>
          Document Reviewing options
        </b>
      </p>
      <p>
        Document reviewing page contains Original document pane and Parsed data pane.
      </p>
      <p>
        Original document pane is displayed in the left pane of the screen.
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          User can navigate between pages using arrows or selecting needed pages in the dropdown list.
        </li>
        <li>
          User can zoom in/out of the document by clicking the '+' and '–' buttons, clicking and dragging the scroll bar,
  using mouse scroll, or typing in the zoom percentage.
        </li>
        <li>
          User can rotate document by 90 degrees clockwise and counter-clockwise via arrows in the upper-left corner.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Parsed data pane is displayed in the right pane of the screen.
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          It contains fields from Model/Template of the document or extracted by user manually.
        </li>
        <li>
          Upon finishing review, user should press 'Complete Review' button.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <Reviewstyles__StyledDocumentReviewImage />
  </FrequentlyAskedQuestionsstyles__HelpAnswer>
</Fragment>
`;
